msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Complete copy of the Qurʼān, written in several different hands (f. [0]-8; f. 9-17; f. 18-30) on several different types of paper; many leaves repaired; the first 30 leaves are later replacements.

respStmt.name: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

supportDesc.extent: 477 leaves : 222 x 160 (160 x 90) mm bound to 220 x 170 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper center recto (1a-252, 252[a]-476); catchwords every verso lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed and vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Textblock ruled in double red and blue with page-opening frame-ruled in single blue; rubrications in red; sūrah headings in red; marginal text division markers and rukūʻ markers in red.

binding.p: Bound in brown leather over thick pasteboard with flap (Type II); embossed paper onlays of a central mandorla, two pendants on the vertical axis, cornerpieces, and triangles between each set of cornerpieces; blind-tooled frame; blue and white chevron pattern endbands.

origin.p: The item is undated and unsigned, possibly completed in the second half of the 18th or 19th century.

history.provenance: Gift of Mayer Sulzberger to the library of the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (note on library bookplate, inside front cover).
Formerly owned by the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (library bookplate inside front cover).
